  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Countable, Sized, java.lang.Comparable<Path<java.lang.String>>, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String>
    public class NetworkPath
extends FilePath
    An abstraction for network paths.

    This class contains numerous methods which down-cast the return value of the superclass to make use easier for clients. Methods that are unique to this class mainly have to do with networks:

    • asUri() - This network path as a URI
    • port() - The port for this network path

    Path Parsing Methods

    • parseNetworkPath(String) - The given string as a network path

    Path Factory Methods

    • networkPath(URI) - A network path for the given URI
    • networkPath(Port, String) - The given port (including host and protocol) and path as a network path
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)

        Returns:
        The subpath of this path starting at given start index (inclusive) and extending to the end index (exclusive). If start and end are equal, the empty path is returned. If start and end are not equal and the path is absolute, the subpath will still be absolute with the same root. If the start and end indexes are invalid, null is returned.
